<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="icon" type="img/png" href="/favicon.png"/>
    <link
      rel="preload"
      href="/fonts/Atkinson/Atkinson-Hyperlegible-Regular.woff2"
      as="font"
      type="font/woff2"
      crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link
      rel="preload"
      href="/fonts/Atkinson/Atkinson-Hyperlegible-Bold.woff2"
      as="font"
      type="font/woff2"
      crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link
      rel="preload"
      href="/fonts/Atkinson/Atkinson-Hyperlegible-Italic.woff2"
      as="font"
      type="font/woff2"
      crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link
      rel="preload"
      href="/fonts/Atkinson/Atkinson-Hyperlegible-BoldItalic.woff2"
      as="font"
      type="font/woff2"
      crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@root/styles/index.scss">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@root/styles/slinky.scss">
    <title>{{ title }}</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
      <details>
        <summary>‚òùÔ∏è Who generated that heading?</summary>
        <p>
          That heading came from a wrapper layout. If you check out this page's source (<code>{{ page.fileSlug }}</code>), you'll notice some frontmatter applied between those
          <code>
            {% raw %}---{% endraw %}
          </code>
          blocks:
        </p>
        <dl>
          <dt>title:</dt>
          <dd>The title we'll apply as the page heading and the browser tab title. You'll see this applied using
            <code>{`{{ title }}`}</code>
            in the layout file described below üëá</dd>
          <dt>layout:</dt>
          <dd>The name of the layout file to apply. In this case,
            <code>layout: layout</code>
            translates to
            <code>_includes/layout.njk</code>
            since 11ty looks in the _includes folder by default.</dd>
        </dl>
        <p>You'll notice this page is wrapped in a layout. This pulls in a few parameters using
          <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/docs/data-cascade/">11ty's data cascade:</a>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <code>title
            </code>
            uses the "title" attribute from our page's front matter.</li>
          <li>
            <code>content | safe
            </code>
            renders our page.</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      {{ content | safe }}
    </main>
  </body>
</html>